// What extra subcommands this binary ships is code, not config.
//
// yours: scaffolded once, never touched again — forge will not overwrite this file
//
// cmd/commands.go is the user-owned cobra extension point — the cmd/
// twin of pkg/app/services.go. The generated root command (cmd/main.go)
// calls userCommands() and registers every returned command before
// Execute(). Generated per-service subcommands live in
// cmd/services_gen.go (a projection of the RegisteredServices rows);
// never list services here.
//
// Use this file for NON-SERVER SHAPES: CLI tools (reports, backfills,
// one-shot admin jobs) and second binaries (a reverse proxy, a queue
// drainer) that ship in the same image as the server but are not Connect
// services. Don't hand-roll a parallel main() with its own timeouts,
// os.Getenv reads, logger, and stdout formatting — that's how cmd/ rots
// into N inconsistent copies. Compose the paved-path pieces instead:
//
//   - Typed config: config.RegisterFlags(cmd) at construction, then
//     `cfg, err := config.Load(cmd)` in RunE — the same env-var + flag
//     surface (flag > env > default) as the server, including cfg.Mode()
//     when you have a config proto (the single dev-mode gate). Source
//     per-command defaults from cfg; reach for forge/pkg/cmdkit.Resolve
//     only for ad-hoc inputs that don't live in the config proto.
//   - forge/pkg/cmdkit for everything a CLI re-invents:
//       cmdkit.Logger / ParseLevel  — a stderr logger fed from cfg
//                                      (stdout stays clean for piped data)
//       cmdkit.OpenDB               — sql.Open + pool tuning + bounded ping
//       cmdkit.ContextWithTimeout   — one bounded context, no literal soup
//       cmdkit.PrintJSON            — indented JSON to stdout (pipe to jq)
//     and observe.WithLogger / FromContext to carry the logger on ctx
//     instead of threading it through every signature.
//   - OTel: `shutdown, metricsHandler, err := setupOTel(ctx)`
//     (cmd/otel.go) wires trace/metric export; `defer shutdown(ctx)`.
//   - Lifecycle: an HTTP-serving sidecar reuses serverkit for the full
//     listener + graceful-shutdown sequence (cmd/server.go is the
//     canonical projection to copy from); a non-HTTP loop derives a
//     signal context via signal.NotifyContext(context.Background(),
//     os.Interrupt, syscall.SIGTERM) and blocks on it.
